ant to use less than the amount of rice wine called for.  Rice vinegar is much stronger than rice wine.  I would suggest mixing all of the other ingredients together first, then adding a little rice vinegar at a time until it tastes balanced to you.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"reply\">\n\t\t\t<a class='comment-reply-link' href='/2011/09/teriyaki-salmon-w-sriracha-mayo/?replytocom=69341#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm(\"comment-69341\", \"69341\", \"respond\", \"13270\")'>Reply</a>\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t</li><!-- #comment-## -->\n\n\t<li class=\"comment even thread-even depth-1\" id=\"comment-69439\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t<div class=\"comment-header\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"comment-author vcard\">\n\t\t\t\t<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/41dc3e007986c35dc46763689fa93174?s=48&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D48&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' />\t\t\t\t<cite class=\"fn\">Anonymous</cite> <span class=\"says\">says:</span>\t\t \t</div>\n\n\t\t\t<div class=\"comment-meta commentmetadata\">\n\t\t\t\t<a href=\"http://www.budgetbytes.com/2011/09/teriyaki-salmon-w-sriracha-mayo/#comment-69439\">09.10.12 at 5:56 pm</a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"comment-content\">\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<p>We had this for dinner tonight and my husband wolfed it down.  We made sriracha mayo &#8211; my first time dabbling with this sauce &#8211; and even though we don&#8217;t eat a ton of spicy things, we both licked our plates clean.  I served it with pineapple chunks and scallion mashed potatoes, because I wanted &#8220;cooling&#8221; things if the spice proved too much for our weak tongues.  Delicious dinner, and we mixed the leftover spicy mayo into the leftover mashed potatoes, and that was incredible, too!  We&#8217;re both now converts to sriracha, and are looking for more ways to use it.  Thank you for this one!</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"reply\">\n\t\t\t<a 