 to catch the splatter&#8230; I&#8217;ve never used one, but it might help! :)</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"reply\">\n\t\t\t<a class='comment-reply-link' href='/2011/09/teriyaki-salmon-w-sriracha-mayo/?replytocom=70085#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm(\"comment-70085\", \"70085\", \"respond\", \"13270\")'>Reply</a>\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t</li><!-- #comment-## -->\n\n\t<li class=\"comment even thread-even depth-1\" id=\"comment-70895\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t<div class=\"comment-header\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"comment-author vcard\">\n\t\t\t\t<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/41dc3e007986c35dc46763689fa93174?s=48&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D48&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' />\t\t\t\t<cite class=\"fn\">Anonymous</cite> <span class=\"says\">says:</span>\t\t \t</div>\n\n\t\t\t<div class=\"comment-meta commentmetadata\">\n\t\t\t\t<a href=\"http://www.budgetbytes.com/2011/09/teriyaki-salmon-w-sriracha-mayo/#comment-70895\">12.03.12 at 4:12 pm</a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"comment-content\">\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<p>Adding a touch of soy sauce (just a small splash) to the mayo/sriracha mix makes for a more melded spicy mayo.  It eliminates the mayo overtones and instead gives you a spicy, creamy, goodness.  </p>\n<p>I came across this trick after repeated attempts to make spicy mayo always came out as mayo flavored with some spice as opposed to the spicy mayo you find at sushi restaurants.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"reply\">\n\t\t\t<a class='comment-reply-link' href='/2011/09/teriyaki-salmon-w-sriracha-mayo/?replytocom=70895#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm(\"comment-70895\", \"70895\", \"respond\", \"13270\")'>Reply</a>\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t</li><!-- #comment-## -->\n\n\t<li class=\"comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1\" id=\"comment-71313\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t<div class=\"comment-header\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"comment-author vcard\">\n\t\t\t\t<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/41dc3e007986c35dc46763689fa93174?s=48&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D48&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' />\t\t\t\t<cite class=\"fn\"><a href='http://www.captainjacksalaska.com/seafood/pc/Wild-Salmon-c3.htm' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Wild Salmon</a></cite> <span class=\"says\">says:</span>\t\t \t</div>\n\n\t\t\t<div class=\"comment-meta commentmetadata\">\n\t\t\t\t<a href=\"http://www.budgetbytes.com/2011/09/teriyaki-salmon-w-sriracha-mayo/#comment-71313\">01.04.13 at 12:48 am</a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"comment-content\">\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<p>We&#8217;ve even done it on the grill and it comes out just as good.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"reply\">\n\t\t\t<a class='comment-reply-link' href='/2011/09/teriyaki-salmon-w-sriracha-mayo/?replytocom=71313#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm(\"comment-71313\", \"71313\", \"respond\", \"13270\")'>Reply</a>\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t</li><!-- #comment-## -->\n\n\t<li class=\"comment even thread-even depth-1\" id=\"comment-71658\">\n\n\t\t\n\t\t<div class=\"comment-header\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"comment-author vcard\">\n\t\t\t\t<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/41dc3e007986c35dc46763689fa93174?s=48&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D48&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' />\t\t\t\t<cite class=\"fn\">Anonymous</cite> <span class=\"says\">says:</span>\t\t \t</div>\n\n\t\t\t<div class=\"comment-meta commentmetadata\">\n\t\t\t\t<a href=\"http://www.budgetbytes.com/2011/09/teriyaki-salmon-w-sriracha-mayo/#comment-71658\">01.19.13 at 5:54 pm</a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"comment-content\">\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<p>Hi Beth!</p>\n<p>If I cook this on the foreman grill, for how long should i leave it on the grill?</p>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t\t<div c